Chile Stocks: Aguas Andinas, Concha y Toro and Empresas La Polar

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-01T15:58:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/chile-stocks-aguas-andinas-concha-y-toro-and-empresas-la-polar.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:12 a.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.3 percent to 4,782.70, ending a four-
session winning streak.  Aguas Andinas SA (AGUAS/A)  (AGUAS/A CC), Chile’s biggest water
utility, rose 1.1 percent to 256.5 pesos, its fifth day of gains
and its longest winning streak in two months. Banco Santander SA
initiated coverage of the stock yesterday with a “buy”
recommendation.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   retreated 15 percent to
600 pesos, its second day of losses. The department store
operator under investigation for irregular consumer loan
practices remains committed to its expansion plans in  Colombia ,
the company’s Chief Executive Officer  Martin Gonzalez  said,
Diario Financiero reported today.  Vina Concha y Toro SA (CONCHA)  , the country’s largest
wine producer and exporter, fell 3.6 percent to 1,220 pesos, the
biggest fall in eight weeks.  Chile ’s peso strengthened today for
a sixth straight day, which signals lower revenue for export-
oriented companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
